<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n03025c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n03" href="#n03025c">N03 (VI.B.3)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n03all.htm#n03025c"> 25(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Beggary Isle / (Wex) / Little Erie</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The lands granted and confirmed by <font color="green">[King Ina of Wessex]</font> include a parcel called &ldquo;Boek Ereie&rdquo; which is frequently mentioned afterwards in grants or otherwise with the addition &ldquo;little Hibernia&rdquo; (parva Hibernia). &ldquo;Boek Ereie&rdquo; is a phonetic rendering of the Gaelic words <mark>&ldquo;beg Eriu,&rdquo; little Ireland</mark>, and there was also a famous islet of that name in Wexford Harbour &mdash; it is still known as <mark>Begery</mark>. <small> Benedict Fitzpatrick, <a name="BFIM" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#BFIM"><cite title="source">Ireland and the Making of Britain</cite></a> (1922) 184-5</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: See also <a name="n03168j" href="n03all.htm#n03168j">N03 (VI.B.3):168(j)</a>. </mm> </dd></dl>
